The schedule of vaccination depends on when the registration process of vaccines will be completed and when the vaccines purchased in Latvia will be delivered. UPDATE: On December 27th 2020 the government debut its list of priority groups, now on the 16th of February 2021, the government is clarifying and changing the priority groupings.

At the suggestion of the Ministry of Health (MoH), the government decided today that in the future the Cabinet of Ministers will decide on the vaccination of certain specific officials in the interests of national security and to ensure the work of public authorities in open sittings according to an approved list.

It was also decided at the government meeting to clarify the sequence of groups of persons to be vaccinated, stipulating that in group 4 teachers and employees of pre-school, special and other educational institutions who work face-to-face and come into close contact with children will be vaccinated together with seniors.

The Cabinet of Ministers will also decide on the priorities for vaccination of people working in different sectors (in groups 5 and 7) on the basis of proposals from the line ministries, as such decisions cannot be within the competence of the MoD.

At the same time, the government has clarified the procedure for vaccinating priority groups - if one of the groups does not meet the previously planned demand, the next group will be vaccinated in parallel, giving preference to those professions that provide full-time employment.

