On June 22, the Latvian government agreed on the new reduced restrictions:
-vaccinated people and people who have had and overcome Covid-19 can gather without restrictions;
-the groups above plus people with negative Covid-19 tests will be able to gather in crowds up to 500 people indoors and up to 1,000 outside;
-those who don't fall into any of the categories will be able to gather up to 20 people indoors and up to 50 outdoors.

These rules were implemented due to yellow' risk level, since the cumulative morbidity has fallen below 100 cases per 100,000 inhabitants over 14 days. However, if the situation returns to high-risk levels and morbidity exceeds 120, the current precautions and safety measures are restored.

