Latvia
October 23rd 2020
The government announced several new guidelines and policies for their mask mandate and social distancing, which will come into effect October 24th and 26th.
They are as follows...


    from 24 October, a maximum of 10 people may be present indoors at private venues and 100 people outdoors. If a private event is held in a public place, such as a restaurant, rented sauna, club, etc., guests must be provided with fixed, personalized seating, a distance of 2 meters (except for persons from one household), and the event can take place until 24.00;
    from 26 October, up to 300 people will be able to gather indoors at public events (the event must have personalized seating and a face mask);
    from 26 October to 15 November, places (non-service) related to indoor children's entertainment (entertainment and amusement centers, children's playrooms, trampoline parks and babysitting rooms, including shopping centers) will be closed;
    from October 26 to November 15, the acquisition of higher education study programs takes place remotely, except for the acquisition of the practical part and clinical practice in the residency.

